About:
 - Sometimes, the first measurement is a little off, about 10 degrees low. I
 am unsure why - perhaps an offset error on the first use of the ADC, or a 
 hysteresis effect of the sensor itself, although thermistors generally have 
 very fast response times.

Resources used, aside from those referenced in the project description:
 - https://www.gnu.org/software/libc/manual/html_node/Waiting-for-I_002fO.html
 	- reference on use of select to check if read on a file descriptor will
	block
 - http://stackoverflow.com/questions/3324078/why-select-always-return-0-after-the-first-timeout
  - help debugging select
